## Goal

**Feature Goal**: A tested `internal/generate/integration_test.go` that exercises the REAL `CommitStaged` end-to-end (real temp git repo + real stub agent binary) across all seven contract paths, asserting outcomes against REAL git plumbing output — the PRD §20.1 layer-3 proof of the snapshot-based atomic-commit core.

**Deliverable**: `internal/generate/integration_test.go` — white-box `package generate`, stdlib + `internal/{config,git,provider,ui}` + the in-package stub helpers (`BuildStubBinary`/`NewStubManifest`/`StubConfig`/`StubResponse`) only; NO testify, NO real LLM. It wires real `*git.Git` + real `*provider.Executor` + a stub Manifest into `Deps` and drives `CommitStaged`, asserting every path with real `git cat-file`/`git log --format=%B`/`git rev-parse`/`git diff --cached --name-only`.

**Success Definition**: `go test ./internal/generate/ -run Integration -v` passes (alongside the existing unit + stub self-tests), `go build ./internal/...`/`go vet ./internal/...`/gofmt are clean, and every contract path is exercised against the REAL git binary with the exact assertions in the table below.

## Why

- **Defensibility proof (PRD §18.1, §20.1 layer 3)**: this is the suite that proves the real `CommitStaged` creates a real commit with the correct TREE/PARENT/message on success and leaves the repo byte-for-byte unchanged (HEAD + index) on every failure path. The unit tests (generate_test.go) prove the two-nested-loop LOGIC via stubs; this suite proves the WIRING against real git + a real exec'd subprocess.
- **Feeds P1.M6.T3.S3**: the §18.1 invariant tests (idempotent index, atomic HEAD, snapshot immutability) compose these same failure-path scenarios. This suite establishes the realistic per-path scenarios + assertion mechanics the invariant suite generalizes.
- **Integration point**: consumed by no production code (test-only artifact). Its OUTPUT is the proof that M2+M3+M4+M5 integrate correctly inside M6's `CommitStaged`.

## What

### User-visible behavior
- A developer runs `go test ./internal/generate/ -run Integration -v` and sees seven subtests that each bootstrap an isolated temp repo, drive the real `CommitStaged`, and assert the exact real-git outcomes (commit created with correct tree/parent/message, or no commit + HEAD/index unchanged on failure).
- Real git is the ONLY thing mocked-out being the agent (the stub binary is exec'd through the real `*provider.Executor` exactly as a real agent would be).

### Success Criteria
- [ ] `integration_test.go` is white-box `package generate`, stdlib + internal/* + in-package stub helpers only (NO testify, NO new external deps, NO real LLM).
- [ ] It wires the REAL `*git.Git` (git.New(dir)) into Deps.Git and the REAL `*provider.Executor` (provider.NewExecutor("")) into Deps.Runner, with a stub Manifest from NewStubManifest and a config from config.Default() — so the full real pipeline (executor→stub binary→stdout→parse→plumbing) is exercised.
- [ ] It covers all 7 paths: SUCCESS; DUP-RETRY-THEN-SUCCESS; PARSE-FAIL-THEN-RESCUE; TIMEOUT; CAS-FAILURE; ROOT-COMMIT; NOTHING-STAGED.
- [ ] SUCCESS asserts (via real git): the returned SHA is a commit object (`git cat-file -t`); its tree line == `git write-tree` of the (unchanged) index; its parent line == the old HEAD; `%B` == Result.Message; stdout contains `[<sha[:7]>] <subject>`.
- [ ] Every FAILURE path asserts HEAD unchanged (`git rev-parse HEAD` before==after) AND index unchanged (`git diff --cached --name-only` before==after); PARSE-FAIL + TIMEOUT render Rescue (candidate ""); CAS-FAILURE prints the §13.5 message and returns ErrHeadMoved (NEVER force, NEVER rescue).
- [ ] CAS-FAILURE moves HEAD deterministically via a test-local `runner` decorator (real git plumbing on `HEAD^{tree}`, NOT `git commit` which would corrupt the staged index).
- [ ] ROOT-COMMIT uses an unborn repo and asserts the commit has NO parent line and HEAD advanced from nothing.
- [ ] NOTHING-STAGED asserts ErrNothingToCommit at the generate layer (the CLI, not generate, auto-stages — v2 seam) with no snapshot taken.

