### Known Gotchas of our codebase & Library Quirks
```go
// CRITICAL (Decision A): the internal/git temp-repo harness (newTempRepo/seedCommits/writeFileStage
// in gittestutil_test.go) is `package git` WHITE-BOX — its symbols are compiled ONLY into the git
// test binary and are NOT importable from `package generate`. `*git.Git` does NOT expose init /
// add <file> / commit (staging POLICY is CLI-only). Drive repo bootstrap via os/exec directly and
// MIRROR the harness conventions (TempDir; git init -q; repo-local user.email/user.name/gpgsign=false).

// CRITICAL (Decision B): this file MUST be `package generate` (white-box) — gitClient and runner
// are PACKAGE-PRIVATE interfaces and the stub helpers live in stubprovider_test.go (package generate).

// CRITICAL (Decision C — CAS): move HEAD DURING Runner.Run with a test-local decorator that advances
// HEAD via PLUMBING on `HEAD^{tree}` (git commit-tree + git update-ref HEAD). NEVER `git commit
// --allow-empty` — that would COMMIT the test's staged file and corrupt the index snapshot. After
// the move, parentSHA (captured by CommitStaged before the loop) != HEAD ⇒ real update-ref exits
// 128 ⇒ ErrHeadMoved; HEAD stays at the decorator's commit; the stagehand commit is DANGLING.

// CRITICAL (Decision D — parse-fail): provider.parseOutput returns ok = (TrimSpace(msg) != "").
// With raw output a NON-EMPTY "garbage" string parses ok=true and would COMMIT (if non-dup), NOT
// rescue. PARSE-FAIL-THEN-RESCUE MUST use StubResponse{Emit:""} on BOTH inner-try entries.

// GOTCHA (StateFile): a multi-entry Script (DUP-RETRY, PARSE-FAIL) REQUIRES a StateFile (per-test
// t.TempDir() path) — without it every invocation selects entry 0 and the counter never advances.

// GOTCHA (TIMEOUT): set cfg.Timeout SMALL (e.g. 500ms) for the TIMEOUT test; the stub {Hang:true}
// blocks via select{} and the executor's real ctx-driven group kill fells it, returning
// *provider.TimeoutError (NOT context.Canceled) ⇒ CommitStaged renders Rescue("") + returns ErrRescue.

// GOTCHA (NOTHING-STAGED): do NOT `git add` anything for this test — StagedDiff returns ("",nil)
// and CommitStaged returns ErrNothingToCommit at the GENERATE layer. The CLI (P1.M7.T2), not
// generate, performs auto-stage-all (v2 seam). No snapshot is taken (no dangling tree).

// GOTCHA (tree verification): after a successful CommitStaged the index is UNCHANGED (commit-tree
// touches no index), so `git write-tree` post-run re-snapshots the SAME tree the commit was built
// from — compare it to the `tree <hash>` line parsed from `git cat-file -p <sha>`.

// GOTCHA (root commit): an unborn repo has NO HEAD; `git rev-parse HEAD` exits 128. The created
// commit's `git cat-file -p <sha>` has NO `parent` line. Seed nothing (leave the repo unborn but
// staged) for the ROOT-COMMIT test.

// GOTCHA (asserting HEAD/index unchanged): capture `git rev-parse HEAD` and
// `git diff --cached --name-only` BEFORE CommitStaged and assert byte-equality AFTER — on every
// failure path this is the §18.1 invariant (the invariant suite P1.M6.T3.S3 will generalize this).

// GOTCHA (no rescue on CAS): the head-moved path prints its OWN §13.5 message and returns
// ErrHeadMoved — it does NOT render Rescue (the commit object exists and is recoverable). Assert
// stderr contains the head-moved message but NOT the rescue block.
```

