## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
- ❌ Don't make the test `package generate_test` — gitClient/runner are package-private and the stub helpers are package-local.
- ❌ Don't reuse internal/git's temp-repo harness — it's white-box `package git`, unreachable from here; mirror its conventions instead.
- ❌ Don't move HEAD with `git commit --allow-empty` in the CAS test — it commits the staged file and corrupts the index; use plumbing on `HEAD^{tree}`.
- ❌ Don't use a non-empty "garbage" Emit for PARSE-FAIL — parseOutput returns ok=true for any non-empty raw string; use Emit="".
- ❌ Don't forget the StateFile on multi-entry scripts — without it every call selects entry 0.
- ❌ Don't assert on a fabricated SHA — verify the commit via real `git cat-file`/`git log --format=%B`/`git rev-parse`.
- ❌ Don't stage anything for NOTHING-STAGED — that path must see an empty diff (StagedDiff returns "").
- ❌ Don't add testify or any external dependency.
- ❌ Don't modify generate.go, the stub binary, or internal/git to make a test pass.
